commit_hash: 24c5da592beabae24bfc5c1deaa3d17d264f5534
schema_version: 0.1.0
intent_summary: Introduce LLM-assisted release-notes generation with configurable
  providers/models, Git Notes storage, reusable markdown/text formatters, and a richer
  `show`/`generate` CLI structure, and update documentation accordingly.
category: feature
behavior_before: The `generate release-notes` command produced simple heuristic, markdown-only
  release notes directly from analyzed artifacts, without LLM synthesis, without configurable
  LLM providers/models, without Git Notes storage, and there was no dedicated way
  to show stored release notes via `gitsummary show release-note`. Impact and changelog
  markdown formatting logic lived inline in the CLI command module.
behavior_after: The `generate release-notes` command now uses LLM-assisted synthesis
  by default (with a `--no-llm` fallback to heuristics), supports `--provider`, `--model`,
  `--product`, `--version`, `--format` (markdown/yaml/text), and `--store` to persist
  release notes into Git Notes attached to the tip commit; markdown/text formatting
  for changelog, impact, and release notes is delegated to shared renderer functions,
  and users can retrieve stored release notes via `gitsummary show release-note <rev>`
  using a new `show` subcommand group. Documentation and getting-started guides are
  updated to describe these capabilities and workflows.
impact_scope: public_api
is_breaking: false
technical_highlights:
- 'Refactors the CLI structure to introduce a `show_app` Typer sub-application: `gitsummary
  show commit <sha>` for commit artifacts and `gitsummary show release-note <rev>`
  for stored release notes, instead of a single flat `show` command.'
- 'Extends the `generate release-notes` command signature with multiple options: `--format/-f`
  (markdown|yaml|text), `--llm/--no-llm`, `--provider/-p`, `--model/-m`, `--product`,
  `--version/-v`, and `--store`, while preserving the core positional `revision_range`
  argument.'
- Introduces integration with an LLM provider abstraction via a helper `_get_llm_provider(provider_name,
  model)` that uses `llm.get_provider`, `llm.list_available_providers`, and a `ProviderConfig`
  object, with graceful fallback to heuristic generation when no provider is available
  or an error occurs.
- Adds logic to infer sensible defaults for `product_name` (repository directory name
  via `repository_root()`, falling back to 'Project') and `version` (parsed from the
  end of the revision range, e.g., `v0.1.0..v0.2.0` â†’ `v0.2.0`).
- Switches release-notes generation from a simple inline markdown builder to a higher-level
  `ReporterService.generate_llm_release_notes(...)` call that returns a `ReleaseNote`
  domain object, which can be serialized to YAML (`to_yaml`) and rendered via shared
  renderer functions (`format_release_note_markdown`, `format_release_note_text`).
- Implements Git Notes persistence for release notes using `save_release_note(tip_sha,
  yaml_content)` under a dedicated namespace (`refs/notes/report/release-note`), and
  reports success with a colored Typer message including the short SHA.
- Moves markdown formatting responsibilities for changelog and impact reports out
  of the CLI command into reusable renderer functions (`format_changelog_markdown`,
  `format_impact_markdown`), simplifying the CLI layer and centralizing presentation
  logic.
- Adds a guard in `generate_release_notes` to detect when no commits in the range
  have been analyzed artifacts, emitting a clear warning and exiting with non-zero
  status to avoid silently generating empty or misleading release notes.
- Updates multiple docs (`README.md`, `getting_started.md`, `current_development_status.md`,
  `TODO.md`) to document LLM-assisted release notes, Git Notes storage, new CLI subcommands
  and flags, and future ideas like interactive refinement, template customization,
  and multi-language support.
tool_version: 0.1.0
